FBIS4-21920 "jptot015__l94085" JPRS-TOT-94-015-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 7 April 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA ISRAEL `Terrorist' Killed After Opening Fire in Ashdod `Terrorist' Killed After Opening Fire in Ashdod One Victim Dies TA0704065294 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 0630 GMT 7 Apr 94 TA0704065294 Tel Aviv IDF Radio Hebrew BFN [Text] Here is an updated report on the terrorist attack at the Ashdod Junction: At least four Israelis were wounded in this attack. Two people were seriously wounded, while another two sustained moderate injuries. The wounded were taken to Rehovot's Kaplan Hospital where the hospital director later told us that one of the casualties had died of his wounds. The nationality of the dead man remains unknown. One of the terrorists was killed, but his accomplice or accomplices managed to escape. According to the reports, the terrorists fired from a bus or car at people standing at a hitchhiking stop at the Ashdod Junction. The dead terrorist was killed by bystanders who shot at him from the junction.
